    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Jan 18<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Dyer</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>The sight of the seeds of Trichosanthes delighted me.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
                    <p> In last Nature there is a Review of Erasmus Darwin, which I think much the best which has appeared &amp; has pleased me greatly.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I can give no sort of reason, but whilst reading it, I kept on thinking that you were the author. If you are not, which is of course the most probable view, pray forgive me for writing; but if you are I am sure that you will not grudge me the pleasure of thanking you heartily for so appreciative &amp; good a review. If you are the author do please tell me; if you are not I shall so understand by your silence.</p>
<p>Yours very sincerley | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12424.xml">letter to W. T. Thiselton-Dyer, 15 January 1880</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD had requested seeds of <hi rend="italic">Trichosanthes anguina</hi> (a synonym of <hi rend="italic">T. cucumerina</hi> subsp. <hi rend="italic">anguina</hi>, snake gourd), or any <hi rend="italic">Trichosanthes</hi>, in his <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12424.xml">letter to W. T. Thiselton-Dyer, 15 January 1880</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">The anonymous review of <hi rend="italic">Erasmus Darwin</hi> was published in <hi rend="italic">Nature</hi>, 15 January 1880, pp. 245–7.</note>
            
        </div>
    
